    {
      "id": "c5694f5a_0e3b5a0b",
      "file_path": "src/test/java/org/onap/aai/rest/SchemaJobStatusControllerTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 56,
      "message": "You can remove the `@Qualifier` here. For that to work, please declare another web client bean in the `WebClientConfiguration` class:\n```java\n  @Lazy\n  @Bean\n  @Primary\n  WebTestClient appClient(@Value(\"${server.port}\") int port) {\n    return WebTestClient.bindToServer()\n      .baseUrl(\"http://localhost:\" + port)\n      .responseTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(300))\n      .defaultHeaders(headers -> {\n        headers.setAccept(Collections.singletonList(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON));\n      })\n      .build();\n  }\n```\nThe `mgmtClient` is not working, because it is binding to the management port. Your controller is exposed on the \"normal\" app port",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7849,
        "name": "Fiete Ostkamp",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "fiete.ostkamp@telekom.de",
        "username": "fostkamp"
      },
      "updated": "2024-11-22 07:40:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
